Sentencas: The rates of electrochemical reactions relevant for use in high-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC) has been investigated as a function of electrode potential, temperature and composition of the gas mixture.
Titulo: THE KINETICS OF ELECTROCHEMICAL REACTIONS ON HIGH-TEMPERATURE FUEL-CELL ELECTRODES

Sentencas: From Arrhenius plots, apparent activation energies, E(a), and apparent pre-exponential factors, A, were calculated for the oxygen-reduction and oxygen-evolution reactions at La0.84Sr0.16MnO3 cathodes.
Titulo: THE KINETICS OF ELECTROCHEMICAL REACTIONS ON HIGH-TEMPERATURE FUEL-CELL ELECTRODES

Sentencas: At low overpotentials (\eta\less-than-or-equal-to 0.2 V), both apparent activation energies and apparent pre-exponential factors are much higher in the temperature range T = 800-1000-degrees-C (E(a) almost-equal-to 160-210 kJ/mol, log A almost-equal-to 6-9) compared with those in the range T= 500-800-degrees-C (E(a) almost-equal-to 80-110 kJ/mol, log A = 2-4).
Titulo: THE KINETICS OF ELECTROCHEMICAL REACTIONS ON HIGH-TEMPERATURE FUEL-CELL ELECTRODES

Sentencas: For oxygen reduction, reaction orders of z(e) = 1 at p(O2) > 0.2 bar and z(e) = 0.5 at p(O2) < 0.2 bar were obtained.
Titulo: THE KINETICS OF ELECTROCHEMICAL REACTIONS ON HIGH-TEMPERATURE FUEL-CELL ELECTRODES

Sentencas: These values may be related to either oxygen adsorbed as molecules or atoms as the reacting species.
Titulo: THE KINETICS OF ELECTROCHEMICAL REACTIONS ON HIGH-TEMPERATURE FUEL-CELL ELECTRODES

Sentencas: From impedance spectroscopy, it follows that the rate of the oxygen-exchange reaction is determined not only by charge transfer, but also by another process, possibly the adsorption or surface diffusion of intermediates.
Titulo: THE KINETICS OF ELECTROCHEMICAL REACTIONS ON HIGH-TEMPERATURE FUEL-CELL ELECTRODES

Sentencas: For the nickel zirconia cermet anode fabricated by wet powder spraying (WPS), an increase in sintering temperature to 1400-degrees-C results in an increase in current density.
Titulo: THE KINETICS OF ELECTROCHEMICAL REACTIONS ON HIGH-TEMPERATURE FUEL-CELL ELECTRODES

Sentencas: A current density of 0.27 A cm-2 at an overvoltage of 0.1 V may be achieved.
Titulo: THE KINETICS OF ELECTROCHEMICAL REACTIONS ON HIGH-TEMPERATURE FUEL-CELL ELECTRODES

Sentencas: From Arrhenius plots, an energy of activation of 130 +/- 10 kJ mol-1 was determined.
Titulo: THE KINETICS OF ELECTROCHEMICAL REACTIONS ON HIGH-TEMPERATURE FUEL-CELL ELECTRODES
